    <h1>Immigrants and unemployment: what official statistics show across 20 countries</h1>
    <p class="intro">In all 20 countries surveyed, immigrants have lower employment rates than native-born residents. The gap ranges from −20 percentage points in Belgium to −3 in Czech Republic, reflecting differences in intake policy, migrant profile, and integration support.</p>
